post_text:
Dear Families,

This month, we are celebrating the publication of the centennial edition of the Aurora, the Newton High School yearbook. For much of the past century, Newton High School was home to students from throughout Sussex County. As such, we would like to invite you to celebrate the history we share on May 31st at 7:00 pm in the high school library. All 100 editions of the yearbook from 1919 to 2019 will be on display as well as other memorabilia from the last century and we hope that you will join us for an evening of nostalgia, shared memories, and refreshments. All parents, students, alumni and members of the Braves community are welcome.

All parents, students, alumni and members of the Braves community are welcome.

post_text:
This is a final reminder for our first ever Family and Community Connection Event on Wednesday March 6th from 6:00-8:00 pm at Merriam Avenue School. This gathering will bring together parents and over 30 local organizations for a wonderful opportunity to meet up and learn about the resources available in our community in the arts and recreation, health care and wellness, social services, school programs, and even from some Alumni All-Stars. We will also offer a taste from several of our local restaurants and give away prizes during the evening.

Families will have the availability of child care for school-aged children as well as shuttle transportation from the following locations in town: 100 Swartswood Rd (Landmark West), 33 Mill St (Brookside), 44 Ryerson Ave (Newton HS), and Trinity St Municipal Lot #4 (directly across from the police station).

We look forward to seeing you on Wednesday evening!
